#compdef assembly-stats
# Documentation: source-direct extraction from upstream
# sanger-pathogens/assembly-stats assembly-stats.cpp
# `usage = "usage: stats [options] ..."` body + the hand-rolled
# `strcmp(argv[ops.infileStartIndex], "-X") == 0` argv-walking
# loop (NOT getopt). Note: the embedded usage prefix says
# `stats` but CMakeLists `add_executable(assembly-stats ...)` +
# `install(TARGETS assembly-stats ...)` confirm the installed
# binary name is `assembly-stats`.
# Reference accessed: 2026-05-30 via gh api.
# sanger-pathogens assembly-stats R143b — Wellcome Sanger
# Institute's reporter of sequence-length statistics from FASTA
# and FASTQ files; pairs with Sanger's broader bioinformatics
# pipeline tools.

_arguments -s -S \
  '-l+[minimum sequence-length cutoff (default 1; shorter sequences ignored)]:length:' \
  '(-t -u)-s[print grep-friendly output]' \
  '(-s -u)-t[print tab-delimited output (with header line)]' \
  '(-s -t)-u[print tab-delimited output without header line]' \
  '-v[print version and exit]' \
  '*:FASTA or FASTQ file:_files -g "*.(fa|fasta|fq|fastq|fa.gz|fasta.gz|fq.gz|fastq.gz)"'
